720209f-a.title: Manhattan: Greenwich Street - Barclay Street
720209f-a.text:
(1)
Greenwich Street, north from Barclay Street, showing the street car tracks being removed by the W. P. A. Overhead is the Ninth Avenue Elevated. This is to be razed sometime in 1940-1. The intersection in the midground is
Park Place.
June 2, 1937
W. P. A. photo
Five Boroughs Project
(2)
Greenwich Street, east side, at Barclay Street and
northward.
L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS  May 7, 1941.

720210f-b.title: Manhattan: Greenwich Street - Barclay Street
720210f-b.text:
Greenwich Street, at Barclay Street and southward, showing details of the 9th Avenue lines station here and its tracks. The photographer is standing on the downtown platform and is viewing eastward. Towering above the uptown unit is the new UU. S. Federal
office Building and Post Office.
June 7, 1940
Views 1,2,3
P. L. Sperr
